(44, 26, 14, 38, 2, 8, 8, 'why persecutest thou me?', 'Connection of Divine Protection', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of divine protection for God''s people. In Acts, the phrase ''why persecutest thou me?'' suggests a deep connection between God and His followers, while Zechariah highlights that those who harm God''s people are touching ''the apple of his eye.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 14, 38, 12, 2, 2, 'persecutest thou me', 'Connection of Persecution and Siege', 'This connection highlights the theme of conflict faced by God''s people. Both passages emphasize the struggle against external forces, with Saul''s persecution of Christians paralleling the siege against Jerusalem.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 14, 46, 10, 22, 22, 'why persecutest thou me', 'Divine Authority and Human Response', 'This connection highlights the theme of human response to divine authority. In Acts, Saul''s persecution provokes a direct confrontation with God, while in Corinthians, the question of provoking the Lord to jealousy suggests a similar dynamic of human actions against divine will.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 14, 20, 13, 15, 15, 'it is hard for thee to kick against the pricks', 'Hardness of Transgression', 'This connection highlights the difficulty of resisting divine guidance. Both passages emphasize that straying from the right path leads to hardship.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
